on an Amazon River Cl. which provided for laytime to run during in and outbound river transit, total claim was for 8.25 days totaling $206k. Vessel was hand selected for Master\u0027s recent experience in the River, this meant she was able to avoid the non compulsory pilot crossing North Bar saving $78k in pilotage from the estimate. Load port being Garyville added $50k to freight but fog delayed the bunker barge forcing us to take our stem outbound. Luckily we were able to find an up river anchorage to take the bunkers which saved us a tug turn in the Mississippi River but lost 24H awaiting the again fog bound barge."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-15T16:30:19.75","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"AMAZON RIVER CLAUSE\n\n-------------------\n\nIF VESSEL LOAD/DISCHARGE AT RIVER PORTS, TIME TO COUNT IN FULL 6 (SIX) HOURS AFTER (UNLESS VESSEL ALL FAST EARLIER) TENDERING NOR AT OCEAN PILOT STATION INBOUND UNTIL DROPPING/PASSING LAST OCEAN PILOT STATION OUTBOUND, IE. NO DEDUCTION FOR TIME LOST DUE TO SHIFT FROM ANCHORAGE TO FIRST BERTH. TIME LOST DUE TO WEATHER AND/OR SEA/RIVER CONDITIONS AND AWAITING TIDE TO BE FOR CHARTERERS\u0027 ACCOUNT."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-01-24T15:21:47.84","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"delay in bunker barge due fog forced outbound stem. able to take at upriver anchorage cancelling a tug turn but another 24h delay for fog before sailing"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-01-17T14:24:25.71","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"vsl arriving 3 days prior generated date - will sit idle awaiting bunkers before laycan // 4 days added at Manaus to account for river pilotage in and out"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}